<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                        <head><hi rend="italic"> Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Shannon</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-03-18"><hi rend="italic">March 18,
                                1893</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 167.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 295 of 10th
                            ultimo, and the draft therewith for $2,500, paid by Salvador in respect
                            of injury to consular property at San Salvador in July 1890, and to
                            Consul H. E. Myers in property and in person.</p>
                        <p>As I have informed the Hon. Mr. Pickler, the Department will retain as
                            payment for the consular property the sum of $137.25 named in Mr.
                            Myers’s letter of February 4, 1891.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>